         <entry xml:id="aksioma-dlgenr"
                xml:lang="en"
                type="mainEntry"
                prev="#eparkhos-dlgenr"
                next="#akhsenai-dlgenr"
                source="Genesis Rabbah">
            <form type="lemma" opt="false">
               <orth type="lemma" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false" select="true">אכסיומא</orth>
               <orth type="transliteration" xml:lang="fjb" opt="false">ʾksywmʾ</orth>
               <pron notation="rabbinic" opt="false">aksiomaʾ</pron>
               <gramGrp opt="false">
                  <gram type="pos" opt="false">noun</gram>
                  <gram type="gen" opt="false">f.</gram>
               </gramGrp>
               <form type="variant" opt="false">
                  <orth type="variant" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false">אכסיומה</orth>
                  <orth type="transliteration" xml:lang="fjb" opt="false">ʾksywmh</orth>
                  <pron notation="rabbinic" opt="false">aksiomah</pron>
               </form>
            </form>
            <sense xml:id="aksioma-dlgenr-1" opt="false">
               <usg type="domain" opt="false"/>
               <usg type="socioCultural" norm="borrowing" opt="false">core borrowing</usg>
               <usg type="normativity" opt="false">standard</usg>
               <usg type="meaningType" opt="false">fig.</usg>
               <usg type="geographic" opt="false">Latin: axiōma</usg>
               <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en" subtype="sense">
                  <quote>authority, honour</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="translationEquivalent" xml:lang="grc">
                  <usg opt="false">
                     <lang opt="false">Ancient Greek</lang>
                  </usg>
                  <quote>ἀξίωμα</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="example" xml:lang="jpa">
                  <quote>ויתחזק ישר' וישב על המטה בשביל לחלוק כבוד למלכות, מיישה בר ברייה דר' יהושע בן לוי [נטל] אכסיומה מן המלכות, כד הוה עלל לבייתיה הווה סביה קאים ליה מן קודמוי בשביל לחלוק כבוד למלכות</quote>
                  <bibl default="false" status="draft">
                     <ref type="witness">97,2</ref>
                     <ref type="witness">III 1242: 17</ref>
                  </bibl>
                  <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                     <quote>And Israel strengthened himself, and sat upon the bed (Gen 48,2) - in order to pay honour to royalty. Miasha, R. Yehoshuaʿ b. Lewi’s grandson, received a post of authority from the Government. Whenever he entered his house his grandfather would rise before him, in order to pay honour to authority. (Freedman / Simon II 934)</quote>
                  </cit>
               </cit>
            </sense>
               <etym type="borrowing" opt="false">
                  <lbl opt="false">source language</lbl>
                  <lang opt="false">Classical Greek</lang>
                  <cit type="etymon" xml:lang="grc">
                     <xr type="related" opt="false">
                        <lbl opt="false">Cf. LSJ</lbl>
                        <ref target="https://www.perseus.tufts.edu/hopper/text?doc=Perseus%3Atext%3A1999.04.0057%3Aentry%3Da)ci%2Fwma"
                           type="entry">ἀξίωμα, A.</ref>
                     </xr>
                  </cit>
               </etym>
            <note anchored="true">
         This meaning supported by <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">AC I 80a</bibl>, <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">MY</bibl> ad loc. <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Jastrow I 64b</bibl> renders “request”, “petition”, similarly also <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Krauss, Fürst 50a</bibl>. This semantics is supported by the context in GenR (not mentioned in the dictionaries). See also <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Sokoloff, SL 44a</bibl> for Syr. <term xml:lang="syc">ܐܟܣܝܘܡܐ</term>
               <term xml:lang="fjb">ʾksywmʾ</term>.
      </note>
            <ref type="bibliography">
